---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Ireland Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/ireland/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'UK for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/united-kingdom' },
  { title: 'Spain for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/spain' },
  { title: 'Portugal for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/portugal' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'irelandFit', header: 'Ireland Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€380-545/mo', irelandFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€445-635/mo', irelandFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€340-485/mo', irelandFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€315-450/mo', irelandFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Irish Private (VHI/Laya)', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€150-350/mo', irelandFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '€340-545', annual: '€4,080-6,540' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '€465-720', annual: '€5,580-8,640' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '€630-970', annual: '€7,560-11,640' },
  { category: 'Irish Public Healthcare', monthly: 'Subsidized', annual: '€50-80/GP visit' },
  { category: 'Irish Private (VHI)', monthly: '€150-350/mo', annual: '€1,800-4,200' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Ireland 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Ireland. Friendly culture, green landscapes, English-speaking, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Ireland"
  subheadline="Ireland offers friendly culture, stunning green landscapes, English language, and EU membership—an increasingly popular retirement destination for those with Irish connections or seeking European living."
  heroImage="/images/countries/ireland-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Ireland</h2>
  <p>
    Ireland offers friendly culture, stunning landscapes, English language, and EU membership. For those with Irish heritage, citizenship by descent is possible. Americans find Ireland familiar yet European. The challenge is cost of living, particularly in Dublin.
  </p>

  <p>
    Dublin offers capital amenities but high costs. Galway provides west coast charm. Cork has second-city character. Kerry offers dramatic scenery. Rural areas provide affordable alternatives. Each region has distinct character and cost profile.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Mixed public/private system</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English (Irish as second)</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> €2,500-5,000/month (~$2,700-5,400); high, especially Dublin</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Mild; rainy; green</li>
      <li><strong>Culture:</strong> Friendly; pub culture; literary</li>
      <li><strong>EU Member:</strong> Free movement for EU citizens</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Ireland Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Ireland has a mixed system—public HSE provides care with charges for most (free for medical card holders). Private hospitals (Blackrock Clinic, Mater Private) offer faster access. Most Irish people have private health insurance to supplement public care. GP visits cost €50-80 without medical card.
  </p>

  <p>
    Over-70s qualify for medical cards if under income threshold. Private insurance (VHI, Laya, Irish Life) provides faster access and choice. International insurance provides additional security. Many residents combine private insurance with public entitlements.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Medical Card for Over-70s</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Over-70s with income below €550/week (single) or €1,050/week (couple) qualify for medical card—free GP, prescriptions, public hospital care. Above threshold may qualify for GP visit card. Private insurance popular for faster access to specialists and procedures.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Ireland has various options:
  </p>

  <h3>EU/EEA Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Free movement—right to live and work in Ireland. Register with immigration for over 3 months.
  </p>

  <h3>Irish Citizenship by Descent</h3>
  <p>
    If grandparent was Irish-born, may be entitled to citizenship. Popular among Irish diaspora, especially Americans.
  </p>

  <h3>Permission to Remain (Retiree)</h3>
  <p>
    For non-EEA retirees with €50,000+ annual income and private health insurance. Leads to long-term residence.
  </p>

  <h3>UK Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Common Travel Area allows UK citizens to live freely in Ireland.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Ireland:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Retiree permission:</strong> Private health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>EU citizens:</strong> EHIC provides public access; private recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical need:</strong> Private important for faster access</li>
    <li><strong>Medical card:</strong> Over-70s may qualify; check eligibility</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Ireland</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      For residents: check medical card eligibility for public; private insurance (VHI, Laya) for faster access. For non-EEA retirees: private insurance mandatory for visa. International coverage provides additional security and flexibility.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Ireland, private coverage important for healthcare access:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Ireland</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Irish network, EU coverage</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>VHI/Laya:</strong> Irish domestic leaders for residents</li>
    <li><strong>Public + medical card:</strong> For those who qualify</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage options for Ireland healthcare.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Ireland vary by coverage type:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Medical card:</strong> Check over-70s eligibility for free public care</li>
    <li><strong>VHI/Laya:</strong> Irish domestic insurers often competitive</li>
    <li><strong>Higher excess:</strong> Reduces private premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Outside Dublin:</strong> Much lower living costs</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Irish-American Returnee, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Irish citizenship by descent. $3,500/month pension. Galway area.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Citizen rights. VHI private + check medical card eligibility.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> VHI ~€280/month. Ancestral homecoming; EU citizenship.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Retiree, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £2,800/month pension. Common Travel Area. Dublin suburb.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> CTA rights. Medical card eligible. Laya private supplement.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Medical card free + Laya ~€220/month. Near UK; EU access.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: German EU Citizen, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €2,800/month pension. EU free movement. Cork area.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> EU rights. Allianz Care international with German backup.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Allianz ~€380/month. English-speaking EU; German healthcare backup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I claim Irish citizenship by descent?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Possibly—if you have an Irish-born grandparent, you may be entitled to citizenship by descent. Must register in Foreign Births Register before claiming. Very popular among Irish-American diaspora. Provides EU citizenship rights. Check eligibility carefully.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Ireland expensive?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—especially Dublin (among Europe most expensive). Housing is major expense. Outside Dublin is more affordable. Budget €2,500-4,500/month for comfortable living. Medical card eligibility helps with healthcare costs. Cost is genuine consideration.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is private insurance worth it?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        For most, yes—Ireland public system has waits for non-emergency care. Private provides faster access to specialists, shorter waits for procedures. About half of Irish people have private insurance. For seniors, faster access often valuable.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about the weather?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Mild but rainy—rarely very cold or hot. "Four seasons in one day" is real. Gulf Stream keeps temperatures moderate. Rain is frequent; sunny days are celebrated. Not a destination for sun-seekers. Green beauty comes from rain.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers with Ireland coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Irish authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
